obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38056)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38056&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Road Transport`
  line `Corporations Act, 1950.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that on and from the commencement of the Delhi Road Transport Laws (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1971, this Act, as amended by the said Act, shall extend to, and be in force in, the Union territory of`
  line `Delhi:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that on and from the commencement of the Road Transport Corporations`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1982, this Act, as amended by the said Act, shall extend to the Union territory of`
  line Mizoram.]
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the Union territory of Delhi" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 2 (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso added by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 2 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38057)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38057&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "ancillary service" means any subsidiary service which provides amenities or facilities to`
  line `persons making use of any road transport service of a Corporation;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "Board" means the Board of Directors of a Corporation;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Corporation" means a Road Transport Corporation established under section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(bb) "Director" means a member of the Board;]`
  line
  line `(c) "extended area" means any area or route to which the operation of any road transport service`
  line `of a Corporation has been extended in the manner provided in section 20;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "road transport service" means a service carrying passengers or goods or both by road in`
  line `vehicles for hire or reward;`
  line
  line `(f) "vehicle" means any mechanically propelled vehicle, used or capable of being used for the`
  line `purpose of road transport, and includes a tram-car, a trolly-vehicle and a trailer;`
  line
  line `(g) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), have the meaning assigned to them in that Act;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by A.O. (No. 3), 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38058)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Road Transport Corporations in the States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "the whole or any part of the State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38058&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The State Government having`
  line `regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the advantages offered to the public, trade and industry by the development of road transport;`
  line
  line `(b) the desirability of co-ordinating any form of road transport with any other form of transport;`
  line
  line `(c) the desirability of extending and improving the facilities for road transport in any area and of`
  line `providing an efficient and economical system of road transport service therein,`
  line
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Road Transport Corporation for ^1[the whole or any`
  line `part of the Union territory of Delhi] under such name as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38059)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Incorporation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38059&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name notified under section 3`
  line `having perpetual succession and a common seal, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38060)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Management of Corporation and Board of Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 3, for section 5 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38060&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Management of Corporation and Board of Directors.--(1) The general superintendence,`
  line `direction and management of the affairs and business of a Corporation shall vest in a Board of Directors`
  line `which, with the assistance of its committees and Managing Director, may exercise all such powers and do`
  line `all such acts and things as may be exercised or done by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of a Chairman and such other Directors, being not less than five and not`
  line `more than seventeen, as the State Government may think fit to appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, if it so thinks fit appoint one of the other Directors as the`
  line `Vice-Chairman of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) Rules made under this Act shall provide for the representation, both of the Central Government`
  line `and of the State Government concerned, on the Board in such proportion as may be agreed to by both the`
  line `Government and of appointment by each Government of its own representatives thereto and where the`
  line `capital of a Corporation is raised by the issue of shares to other parties under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 23, provision shall also be made for the representation of such shareholders on the Board and the`
  line `manner in which the representatives shall be elected by such shareholders.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of and the manner of filling casual vacancies among the Directors shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38061)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Disqualifications for being chosen as, or for being, a Director of a Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38061&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Disqualifications for being chosen as, or for being, a ^1[Director of a Corporation].--^2[(1)] A`
  line `person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, or for being, a ^1[Director of a Corporation[--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is found to be a lunatic or a person of unsound mind; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he has been adjudged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he has been convicted of an offence involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) if he has, directly or indirectly, any interest in any subsisting contract made with, or in any`
  line `work being done for, the Corporation except as a shareholder (other than a director) in an`
  line `incorporated company, provided that where he is a shareholder he shall disclose to the State`
  line `Government the nature and extent of shares held by him in such company; or`
  line
  line `(e) if he has any financial interest in any other road transport undertaking.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Nothing in clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be deemed to disqualify the ^4[Managing Director]`
  line `of a Corporation for being chosen as, or for being, a`
  line `^5[Director] thereof.]`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Nothing in clause (e) of sub-section (1) shall be deemed to disqualify,--`
  line
  line `(a) any officer or other employee of the Government for being chosen as, or for being, a Director`
  line `of a Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) any officer or other employee of a Corporation for being chosen as, or for being, a Director of`
  line `another Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "member of a Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Section 6 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 28 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 4, for "Chief Executive Officer or General Manager" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "member" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38062)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Resignation of office by the Chairman or a Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "member" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38062&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `7. Resignation of office by the Chairman or a ^1[Director].--The Chairman or any other ^1[Director]`
  line `of a Corporation may resign his office by giving notice in writing to the State Government and, on such`
  line `resignation being accepted by that Government, shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38063)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Removal of Chairman and members from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38063&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The State Government may remove`
  line `from office the Chairman or any other ^2[Director] of the Corporation who--`
  line
  line `(a) is or becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 6; or`
  line
  line `(b) without excuse sufficient in the opinion of the State Government is absent for more than four`
  line `consecutive meetings of the ^3[Board].`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(2) The State Government may terminate the appointment of any Director after giving him notice`
  line `for such period (being not less than one month) as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appointment of a Director appointed by the Central Government shall not be`
  line `terminated under this sub-section without the concurrence of that Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 8 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "member" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 5 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38113)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies amongst members or defect in the constitution not to invalidate acts or proceedings of a Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38113&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of a ^1[Corporation or its Board] shall be invalid`
  line `by reason only of the existence of any vacancy ^2[in its Board] or any defect in the constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "amongst its members" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38065)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Temporary association of persons with a Board for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38065&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1)10. Temporary association of persons with a ^1[Board] for particular purposes.-- A ^1[Board]`
  line `may associate with itself for any particular purpose in such manner as may be determined by regulations`
  line `made under this Act any person whose assistance or advice it may desire.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the ^1[Board] under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a`
  line `right to take, part in the discussions of the ^1[Board] relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to`
  line `vote at a meeting of the ^1[Board].`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38066)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Meetings of Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38066&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) 11. Meetings of ^1[Board].-- A ^1[Board] shall meet at such times and places and shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), observe such rules of procedure in regard to transaction of`
  line `business at its meetings as may be provided by regulations made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1[Board] shall meet at least once in every three months.`
  line
  line `(2) The person to preside at a meeting of a ^2[Board] shall be the Chairman thereof, or in his`
  line `absence from any meeting, the Vice-Chairman, if any, or in the absence of both the Chairman and the`
  line `Vice-Chairman, ^3[such Director as may be chosen by the Directors present] from among themselves to`
  line preside.
  line
  line `(3) All questions at a meeting of a ^2[Board] shall be decided by a majority of votes of the members`
  line `present, and in the case of equality of votes, the Chairman or, in his absence, any other person presiding`
  line `shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "such member as may be chosen by the members present" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line `1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38067)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to appoint committees and delegate functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38067&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] A ^2[Board] may, from time to`
  line `time by resolution passed at a meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint committees ^3[consisting of Directors] for performing such functions as may be`
  line `specified in the resolution;`
  line
  line `(b) delegate to any such committee or to the ^4[Chairman, Vice-Chairman, Chief Executive`
  line `Officer, the General Manager, the Deputy General Manager or the Chief Accounts Officer of the`
  line `Corporation] subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the resolution,`
  line `such of its powers and duties as it may think fit;`
  line
  line `(c) authorised the ^5[Managing Director] ^6[or any other officer of the Corporation] subject to such`
  line `such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the resolution to exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such duties as it may deem necessary for the efficient day-to-day administration of its`
  line business.
  line
  line `^7[(2) The Chairman, Vice-Chairman or Managing Director may delegate any of his powers and duties`
  line `duties [including powers and duties delegated to him under sub-section (1)] to any officer of the Corporation, and the officer to whom such powers and duties are delegated, shall exercise and perform such`
  line `powers and duties under the control and supervision of the Managing Director.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 12 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "of its members" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "Chairman or Vice-Chairman" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 6, for "Chief Executive Officer or General Manager" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 6 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38068)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for s. 13 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38068&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[13. Authentication of orders and other instruments.--All orders and decisions of the Board`
  line `shall be authenticated by the signature of the Secretary or by any such other officer of the Corporation as`
  line `may be authorised in this behalf by the Board or under the regulations made under section 45 and all other`
  line `instruments issued by a Board shall be authenticated by the signature of the Managing Director or any`
  line `other officer of the Corporation authorised in like manner in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38069)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Officers and servants of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38069&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every Corporation shall have a Managing`
  line `Director, a Chief Accounts Officer and a Financial Adviser, appointed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the same person may be appointed as the Chief Accounts Officer and the Financial`
  line Adviser.]
  line
  line `(2) A Corporation may appoint ^2[a Secretary and such other officers and employees] as it considers`
  line `necessary for the efficient performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) The conditions of appointment and service and the scales of pay of the officers and employees of`
  line `of a Corporation shall--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects the Managing Director, the Chief Accounts Officer and the Financial Adviser, or,`
  line `as the case may be, the Chief Accounts Officer-cum-Financial Adviser, be such, as may be`
  line `prescribed, and`
  line
  line `(b) as respects the other officers and employees, be such, as may, subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 34, be determined by regulations made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "such other officers and servants" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 8, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38070)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Managing Director, Chief Accounts Officer and Financial Adviser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38070&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Managing Director, Chief Accounts Officer and Financial Adviser.--(1) The Managing`
  line `Director shall be the executive head of the Corporation and all other officers and employees of the`
  line `Corporation shall be subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Managing Director shall obtain the views of the Chief Accounts Officer and the Financial`
  line `Adviser or, as the case may be, the Chief Accounts Officer-cum-Financial Adviser, on every proposal`
  line `involving revenues, or expenditure from the fund, of the Corporation and shall cause such views to be`
  line `placed before the Board prior to the consideration of such proposal by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38071)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `General disqualification of all officers and servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "officer or servant" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38071&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No person who has directly or`
  line `indirectly, by himself or his partner or agent, any share or interest in any contract, by or on behalf of a`
  line `Corporation, or in any other road transport undertaking shall become or remain an ^1[officer or other`
  line `employee] of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38072)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment of Advisory Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38072&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, after ascertaining the views of`
  line `the Corporation, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute one or more Advisory Councils`
  line `consisting of such number of persons, on such terms, and for the purpose of advising the Corporation on`
  line `such matters, as may be specified in that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (38073)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 18
  title `Establishment of subsidiary corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38073&sectionno=17A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Establishment of subsidiary corporations.--(1) Where a Corporation (hereinafter in this`
  line `section referred to as the parent Corporation) is satisfied that it is expedient or necessary so to do for the`
  line `more efficient discharge of its functions under this Act, it may, with the concurrence of the State`
  line `Government and the Central Government, frame by notification in the Official Gazette a scheme or`
  line `schemes providing for the establishment of one or more subsidiary corporations.`
  line
  line `(2) A scheme framed under sub-section (1) shall specify the subsidiary corporation or corporations`
  line `which shall become established thereunder, the date or dates with effect from which they shall be so`
  line `established, the powers and functions of the parent Corporation which such subsidiary corporation or`
  line `corporations may exercise and discharge, the conditions and limitations subject to which such powers`
  line `may be exercised, the management of the affairs of each such subsidiary corporation by a Board of`
  line `Directors, the capital of each such subsidiary corporation and all other matters relating to such subsidiary`
  line `corporations corresponding to the various matters for which provisions have been made in this Act with`
  line `respect to the parent Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no subsidiary corporation shall start operation on any new route without the previous approval`
  line `of the parent Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) the representatives of the Central Government on the Board of Directors of a subsidiary`
  line `corporation shall be in proportion to its contribution to the capital of the parent Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) the liability of the Central Government to provide contribution to the capital of the subsidiary`
  line `corporation or to the parent Corporation shall not be increased without the approval of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) a subsidiary corporation shall have a Managing Director, a Chief Accounts Officer and a`
  line `Financial Adviser or a Chief Accounts Officer-cum-Financial Adviser, and such officers shall be`
  line `appointed by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(e) the State Government and the parent Corporation shall have power to give directions to a`
  line `subsidiary corporation in respect of any matter, including directions relating to recruitment conditions`
  line `of service and training of the employees of the subsidiary corporation, wages to be paid to such`
  line `employees, reserves to be maintained by the subsidiary corporation;`
  line
  line `(f) the capital budget, the revenue budget and the annual development plans of a subsidiary`
  line `corporation shall be submitted for approval to the parent Corporation and where such budget or plan`
  line `involves any deficit, also to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every subsidiary corporation established under a scheme framed under sub-section (1) shall be a`
  line `body corporate, by the name specified in the scheme having perpetual succession and a common seal and`
  line `shall by the said name sue and be sued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38074)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `General duty of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "State or part of the State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38074&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the general duty of a Corporation so to exercise its`
  line `powers as progressively to provide or secure or promote the provision of, an efficient, adequate,`
  line `economical and properly co-ordinated system of road transport services in the ^1[Union territory of Delhi`
  line `or part thereof] for which it is established and in any extended area:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be construed as imposing on a Corporation, either directly`
  line `or indirectly, any form of duty or liability enforceable by proceedings before any Court or Tribunal to`
  line `which it would not otherwise be subject.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38075)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38075&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a Corporation shall have`
  line power--
  line
  line `(a) to operate road transport services in the ^1[Union territory of Delhi] and in any extended area;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide for any ancillary service;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide for its employees suitable conditions of service including fair wages, establishment`
  line `of provident fund, living accommodation, places for rest and recreation and other amenities;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) to authorise the issue of passes to its employees and other persons either free of cost or at`
  line `concessional rates and on such conditions as it may deem fit to impose;`
  line
  line `(e) to authorise the grant of refund in respect of unused tickets and concessional passes.]`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the powers conferred by sub-section (1) shall include`
  line power--
  line
  line `(a) to manufacture, purchase, maintain and repair rolling stock, vehicles, appliances, plant, equipment or any other thing required for the purpose of any of the activities of the Corporation referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, the expression "manufacture" does not include the construction of`
  line `the complete unit of a motor vehicle except for purposes of experiment or research;`
  line
  line `(b) to acquire and hold such property, both movable and immovable, as the Corporation may`
  line `deem necessary for the purpose of any of the said activities, and to lease, sell or otherwise transfer`
  line `any property held by it;`
  line
  line `(c) to prepare schemes for the acquisition of, and to acquire, either by agreement or compulsorily`
  line `in accordance with the law of acquisition for the time being in force in the ^3[Union territory of Delhi]`
  line `and with such procedure as may be prescribed, whether absolutely or for any period, the whole or any`
  line `part of any undertaking of any other person to the extent to which the activities thereof consist of the`
  line `operation of road transport services in ^4[that Union territory] or in any extended area;`
  line
  line `(d) to purchase by agreement or to take on lease or under any form of tenancy any land and to`
  line `erect thereon such buildings as may be necessary for the purpose of carrying on its undertaking;`
  line
  line `(e) to authorise the disposal of scrap vehicles, old tyres, used oils, ^5[any other stores of scrap`
  line `value, or such other stores as may be declared to be obsolete in the prescribed manner].`
  line
  line `(f) to enter into and perform all such contracts as may be necessary for the performance of its`
  line `duties and the exercise of its powers under the Act;`
  line
  line `(g) to purchase vehicles of such type as may be suitable for use in the road transport services`
  line `operated by the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(h) to purchase or otherwise secure by agreement vehicles, garages, sheds, office buildings,`
  line `depots, land, workshops, equipment, tools, accessories to and spare parts for vehicles, or any other`
  line `article owned or possessed by the owner of any other undertaking for use thereof by the Corporation`
  line `for the purposes of its undertaking;`
  line
  line `(i) to do anything for the purpose of advancing the skill of persons employed by the Corporation`
  line `or the efficiency of the equipment of the Corporation or of the manner in which that equipment is`
  line `operated, including the provision by the Corporation, and the assistance by the Corporation to others`
  line `for the provision of facilities or training, education and research;`
  line
  line `(j) to enter into and carry out agreements with any person carrying on business as a carrier of`
  line `passengers or goods providing for the carriage of passengers or goods on behalf of the Corporation by`
  line `that other person at a thorough fare or freight.`
  line
  line `(k) to provide facilities for the consignment, storage and delivery of goods;`
  line
  line `(l) to enter into contracts for exhibition of posters and advertising boards on and in the vehicles`
  line `and premises of the Corporation and also for advertisement on tickets and other forms issued by the`
  line `Corporation to the public;`
  line
  line `(m) with the prior approval of the State Government to do all other things to facilitate the proper`
  line `carrying on of the business of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `^6[(n) to determine with the previous approval of the State Government, and in case of a road`
  line `transport service operated in any extended area, also with the previous approval of the Government of`
  line `the State within which such extended area is situated, fares and freights for the carriage of passengers`
  line `and goods in any road transport service provided by the Corporation.]`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be construed as authorising a Corporation, except with the previous`
  line `approval of the State Government--`
  line
  line `(i) to manufacture or maintain anything which is not required directly or indirectly for use for the`
  line `purpose of the undertaking of the Corporation or to repair, store, or provide any service for, any`
  line `vehicle which does not belong to the Corporation or is not used directly or indirectly for the purpose`
  line `of its undertaking;`
  line
  line `(ii) to purchase any vehicle for the purpose of sale to another person;`
  line
  line `(iii) to sell or supply to any person lubricants, spare parts, or equipment for or accessories to,`
  line vehicles;
  line
  line `(iv) to let vehicles on hire for the carriage of passengers or goods except as expressly provided by`
  line `or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Except as otherwise provided by this Act nothing in the foregoing provisions shall be construed as`
  line `authorising the Corporation to disregard any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a Corporation acquires the whole or any part of an undertaking of any other person, the`
  line `Corporation shall, in appointing its ^7[officers and other employees] take into consideration the claims of`
  line `employees employed in that undertaking.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall not be construed as limiting any power of a Corporation`
  line `conferred by or under any subsequent provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid., for "State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959) .`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "State concerned" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid., for "that State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 11, for "or any other stores of scrap value" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 13-11-1971).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 11, for "officers and servants" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (38076)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 21
  title `Disposal of unclaimed articles and property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38076&sectionno=19A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Disposal of unclaimed articles and property.--(1) When any articles or goods have come`
  line `into the possession of a Corporation for carriage or otherwise and are not claimed by the owner or any`
  line `other person appearing to the Corporation to be entitled thereto, the Corporation shall, if such owner or`
  line `other person is known, cause a notice to be served upon him requiring him to remove the articles or goods`
  line `within seven days of the service of such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If such owner or other person is not known or the notice cannot be served upon him or he does not`
  line `comply with the requisition in the notice, the Corporation may, after the expiration of such period as may`
  line `be specified by regulation made under this Act, sell the articles or goods by public auction and shall, after`
  line `deducting from the sale-proceeds expenses for holding the sale or any amount which may be due to the`
  line `Corporation, credit the surplus sale-proceeds, if any, to the Fund of the Corporation; and the`
  line `sale-proceeds so credited may be paid on demand to any person who establishes his right thereto in a`
  line `court of competent jurisdiction or within one year of such sale to the satisfaction of the Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_b:
  sectionId (38077)
  sectionNo 19B
  orderNo 22
  title `Corporation to obtain the approval of the Central Government in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38077&sectionno=19B&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_19_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[19B. Corporation to obtain the approval of the Central Government in certain cases.--In the`
  line `exercise of any of its powers under this Act, the Corporation shall not incur on any single work, service or`
  line `scheme or for any other purpose a capital expenditure of more than twenty-five lakhs of rupees except`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38114)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Extension of the operation of the road transport service of a Corporation to areas within another State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38114&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a Corporation considers it to be expedient in the public interest to extend the`
  line `operation of any of its road transport services to any route or area situated within another State, it may,`
  line `with the permission of the State Government, negotiate with the Government of the other State regarding`
  line `the proposed extension.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Government of the other State approves the proposed extension, the Corporation shall`
  line `prepare a scheme for the purpose and forward the same to the other Government for its consent, and after`
  line `such consent has been received, the Corporation may, with the previous approval of the State`
  line `Government, sanction the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) After the scheme has been so sanctioned, it shall be competent for the Corporation to extend the`
  line `operation of its road transport service to such route or area and when the operation of such service is so`
  line `extended, the Corporation shall operate the service on that route or in that area subject to the provisions of`
  line `any law in force in the other State within which such route or area is situated.`
  line
  line `(4) The Corporation may, from time to time, alter or extend the scheme sanctioned under`
  line `sub-section (2) by a supplementary scheme prepared and sanctioned in the manner provided in the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38079)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Carriage of mails.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38079&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), a Corporation shall, if so required by the Central Government, carry mails at such`
  line `rates and on such terms and conditions as may be specified in this behalf by ^1[that Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "The Central Government in consultation with the State`
  line `Government" (w.e.f. 13-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38080)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `General principle of Corporation’s finance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38080&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the general principle of a Corporation`
  line `that in carrying on its undertaking it shall act on business principles.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38081)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Capital of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38081&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The State Government may provide to a Corporation`
  line `established by that Government any capital that may be required by the Corporation for the purpose of`
  line `carrying on its undertaking or for purposes connected therewith on such terms and conditions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as that Government may determine.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Corporation may, whether or not any capital is provided to it under sub-section (1), raise by`
  line `the issue of shares such capital (hereafter in this section referred to as the authorised share capital) as`
  line `may be authorised in this behalf by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any capital is provided to the Corporation under sub-section (1), no capital may`
  line `be raised under this sub-section without the previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2A) Any capital raised under sub-section (2) with the previous approval of the Central Government`
  line `may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) in addition to the capital provided to the Corporation under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) subscribed to by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, by`
  line `converting the whole or any part of the capital provided [whether before or after the commencement`
  line `of the Road Transport Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1982] to the Corporation by that Government`
  line `under sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(3) The ^3[authorised share capital] of the Corporation shall be divided into such number of shares as`
  line `the State Government may determine; and the number of shares which shall be subscribed by the State`
  line `Government, ^4*** and other parties (including persons whose undertakings have been acquired by the`
  line `Corporation) shall also be determined by the State Government ^4***.`
  line
  line `(4) The allotment of shares to other parties mentioned in sub-section (3) shall be made by the`
  line `Corporation in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The shares of the Corporation shall not be transferable except in accordance with the rules made`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The Corporation may at any time, with the previous approval of the State Government, redeem the`
  line `shares issued to the other parties under sub-section (4) in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7 (a) and the First Schedule, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-11`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 12, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "authorised capital" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38082)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Additional capital of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38082&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `If, after the issue of shares under section 23 a`
  line `Corporation requires any further capital, the Corporation may, with the previous sanction of the State`
  line `Government, raise such additional capital by the issue of new shares and the provisions of sub-sections`
  line `(2),`
  line `^1[(2A)] (3), (4), (5) and (6) of the said section shall apply to the issue of such shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38083)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 28
  title `Guarantee by the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38083&sectionno=25&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The shares of a Corporation shall be guaranteed by the`
  line `State Government as to the payment of the principal and the payment of the annual dividend at such`
  line `minimum rate as may be fixed by the State Government by notification published in the Official Gazette`
  line `at the time of issuing the shares.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38084)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 29
  title `Borrowing powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 13, for section 26 (we.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38084&sectionno=26&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Borrowing powers.--A Corporation may, with the previous approval of the State Government,`
  line `borrow money for the purpose of raising its working capital or meeting any expenditure of a capital`
  line `nature in the open market or from a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), a State Finance`
  line `Corporation, established under section 3 of the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), the`
  line `Industrial Finance Corporation of India, established under section 3 of the Industrial Finance Corporation`
  line `Act, 1948 (15 of 1948), the Industrial Development Bank of India, established under section 3 of the`
  line `Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964), the Life Insurance Corporation of India,`
  line `established under section 3 of the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956 (31 of 1956), or any other`
  line `financial institution providing credit which is subject to the control of the Reserve Bank of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38085)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 30
  title `Fund of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38085&sectionno=27&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Corporation shall have its own fund and all receipts of the`
  line `Corporation shall be carried thereto and all payments by the Corporation shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise directed by the State Government, all moneys belonging to that fund shall be`
  line `deposited in the Reserve Bank of India or with the agents of the Reserve Bank of India,`
  line `^1[or with the`
  line `corresponding new banks constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980)] or invested in such securities as may be approved by`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38086)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 31
  title `Payment of interest and dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38086&sectionno=28&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where ^1[the whole or part of the capital of a`
  line `Corporation] is provided by the Central Government and the State Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23, the Corporation shall pay interest on such capital at such rate as may, from time to time, be`
  line `fixed by the State Government ^2*** and such interest shall be deemed to be a part of the expenditure of`
  line `the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Corporation`
  line `^3[raises the whole or any part of its capital] by issue of shares, it shall pay`
  line `dividend on such shares at such rate as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Corporation, subject to`
  line `any general limitations which may have been imposed by the State Government ^2***, and such dividend`
  line `shall be deemed to be a part of the expenditure of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "the capital of a Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "raises its capital" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38087)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 32
  title `Provision for depreciation and reserve and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38087&sectionno=29&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Corporation shall make such`
  line `provisions for depreciation and for reserve and other funds as the State Government may, from time to`
  line `time, direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The management of the said funds, the sums to be carried from time to time to the credit thereof`
  line `and the application of the moneys comprised therein shall be determined by the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fund shall be utilised for any purpose other than that for which it was created`
  line `without the previous approval of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (38088)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title `Disposal of net profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38088&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `After making provision for payment of interest and dividend under`
  line `section 28 and for depreciation, reserve and other funds under section 29, a Corporation may utilise such`
  line `percentage of its net annual profits as may be specified in this behalf by the State Government for the`
  line `provision of amenities to the passengers using the road transport services, welfare of labour employed by`
  line `the Corporation and for such other purposes as may be prescribed with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, ^2[and out of the balance such amount as may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `State Government ^1***, be specified in this behalf by the Corporation, may be utilised for financing the`
  line `expansion programmes of the Corporation and the remainder, if any, shall be made over to the State`
  line `Government for the purpose of road development].`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 6, for "and the balance shall be made over to the State Government for the purpose of road`
  line `development" (w.e.f. 1-9-1959)`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (38089)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power of the Corporation to spend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38089&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `A Corporation shall have power to spend such sums as it`
  line `thinks fit on objects authorised under this Act and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out`
  line `of the fund of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (38090)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 35
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 7, for "A Corporation may sanction" (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38090&sectionno=32&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Corporation shall, by such date in each year as may be prescribed, prepare`
  line `and submit to the State Government for approval a budget for next financial year showing the estimated`
  line `receipts and expenditure during that financial year in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), no sum shall be expended by or on behalf of`
  line `a Corporation unless the expenditure of the same is covered by a current budget grant approved by the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(3)`
  line `^1[Subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government, a Corporation may sanction] any re-appropriation within the grant from one head of the`
  line `expenditure to another or from a provision made for one scheme to that in respect of another, subject to`
  line `the condition that the aggregate budget grant is not exceeded.`
  line
  line `(4) A Corporation may, within such limits and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, incur`
  line `expenditure in excess of the limit provided in the budget approved by the State Government under any`
  line `head of expenditure or in connection with any particular scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (38091)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38091&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[33. Accounts and audit.--(1) The Corporation shall maintain proper accounts and other records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts including the profit and loss account and the balance sheet in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of a Corporation shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India or his nominee and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Corporation to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of a Corporation shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of`
  line `the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Corporation as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the State Government; and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before ^2[each`
  line `House of Parliament].]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 33 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "the Legislature of the State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (38092)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Directions by the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38092&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, after consultation with a`
  line `Corporation established by such Government, give to the Corporation general instructions to be followed`
  line `by the Corporation, and such instructions may include directions relating to the recruitment, conditions of`
  line `service and training of its employees, wages to be paid to the employees, reserves to be maintained by it`
  line `and disposal of its profits or stocks.`
  line
  line `(2) In the exercise of its powers and performance of its duties under this Act, the Corporation shall`
  line `not depart from any general instructions issued under sub-section (1) except with the previous permission`
  line `of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (38093)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38093&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Corporation shall furnish to the State Government such returns,`
  line `statistics, accounts and other information with respect to its property or activities or in regard to any`
  line `proposed scheme as the State Government may from time to time require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), a Corporation shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after the end of each financial year, submit to the ^1[State Government] a report on the exercise and`
  line `performance by it of its powers and duties under this Act during that year and on its policy and`
  line programme.
  line
  line `^2[(3) The State Government shall cause the annual report referred to in sub-section (2) to be laid`
  line `before ^3[each House of Parliament].]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "Central and the State Governments" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "the Legislature of the State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (38094)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to order inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38094&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government, with a view to satisfy itself that the`
  line `powers and duties of a Corporation established by that Government are being exercised and performed`
  line `properly, may, at any time, appoint any person or persons to make inquiries into all or any of the activities`
  line `of the Corporation and to report to the State Government the result of such inquiries.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall give to the person or persons so appointed all facilities for the proper`
  line `conduct of the inquiries and shall produce before, or furnish to, the person or persons any document,`
  line `account or information in the possession of the Corporation which such person or persons demand for the`
  line `purposes of the inquiries.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (38095)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power to control a part of the undertaking of a Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38095&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) If on receipt of the report of`
  line `any inquiry held under section 36 or otherwise, the State Government is satisfied that it is necessary so to`
  line `do in the public interest, the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise any`
  line `person to take over from the Corporation, and so long as that notification is in force, to administer in`
  line `accordance with such directions as may be issued from time to time by the State Government such part of`
  line `the undertaking of the Corporation as may be specified in the notification, and any person so authorised`
  line `may, for the purpose of so administering the said part of the undertaking exercise all or any of the powers`
  line `of the Corporation or of any officer of the Corporation under this Act, issue such directions as he thinks`
  line `fit to the ^1[officers or other employees] of the Corporation and employ any outside agency.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may by such notification direct that all charges and expenses incurred by`
  line `the person so authorised together with such remuneration as the State Government may allow from time`
  line `to time to such person shall be paid within such time as may be fixed by the State Government from the`
  line `fund of the Corporation, and if the expenses are not so paid, the State Government may make an order`
  line `directing the persons having the custody of that fund to pay to the person so authorised such expenses in`
  line `priority to any other charges against such fund and he shall, so far as the funds to the credit of the`
  line `Corporation admit, comply with the order of the State Government.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every notification issued under this section together with a report on the circumstances leading`
  line `to its issue shall be laid before ^3[each House of Parliament], as soon as may be, after it is issued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "officers or servants" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-19-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "the Legislature of the State" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (38096)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to supersede a Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38096&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the State Government is of opinion that a`
  line `Corporation established by that Government is unable to perform, or has persistently made default in the`
  line `performance of the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act or has exceeded or abused`
  line `its powers, the State Government may, ^1*** by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the`
  line `Corporation for such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section the State Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable time to the Corporation to show cause why it should not be superseded and shall consider the`
  line `explanation and objections, if any, of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding a Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) all the ^2[Directors] of the Corporation shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their`
  line `offices as such a ^2[Directors];`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act or of any other`
  line `law, be exercised or performed by or on behalf of the Corporation shall, during the period of`
  line `supersession, be exercised and performed by such person or persons as the State Government may`
  line direct;
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in the Corporation shall, during the period of supersession, vest in the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the State Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further term as it may consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) reconstitute the Corporation in the manner provided in section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous approval of the Central Government," omitted by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "members" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (38097)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Liquidation of a Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, for "Central and the State Government" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38097&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) No provision of any law relating to the winding up of`
  line `companies or corporations shall apply to a Corporation, and no Corporation shall be placed in liquidation`
  line `save by order of the State Government concerned and save in such manner as may be directed by that`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made by any State Government except with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of a Corporation being placed in liquidation, the assets of the Corporation, after`
  line `meeting the liabilities, if any, shall be divided among the ^1[State Government] and such other parties, if`
  line `any, as may have subscribed to the capital in proportion to the contribution made by each of them to the`
  line `total capital of the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (38098)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 43
  title `Compensation for acquisition of road transport undertakings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38098&sectionno=40&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a Corporation`
  line `acquires under this Act the whole or any part of any undertaking, there shall be paid by the Corporation`
  line `compensation the amount of which shall be determined in the manner and in accordance with the`
  line `procedure hereinafter set out, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the amount of compensation can be fixed by agreement, it shall be paid in accordance`
  line `with such agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the amount shall be determined by an arbitral`
  line `Tribunal consisting of one nominee of the Corporation, one nominee of the person to be`
  line `compensated, and a Chairman to be nominated by the Chief Justice of the ^1[High Court of Delhi];`
  line
  line `(c) an appeal shall ^2[lie to the High Court of Delhi] against the decision of the Tribunal and the`
  line `^3[order of that High Court] on such appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid@i/@., for "High Court exercising jurisdiction in relation to the State concerned"`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid., for "lie to the High Court" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7(a) and the First Schedule, ibid., for "order of the High Court" (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (38115)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 44
  title `Omitted .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38115&sectionno=41&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `[Corporation to be deemed to be a local authority and provision as to third party`
  line `risks].--Omitted by the Road Transport Corporations (Amendment) Act, 1959 (28 of 1959),`
  line `s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (38116)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power of entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "officer or servant" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38116&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it is necessary for a Corporation to carry out any of its works or to`
  line `make any survey, examination or investigation, preliminary or incidental to the exercise of powers or the`
  line `performance of duties by the Corporation under this Act, any ^1[officer or other employee] of the`
  line `Corporation generally or specially empowered by the Corporation may, with the previous permission of the District Magistrate, enter upon any land or premises between sunrise and sunset, after giving reasonable notice of the intention to make such entry to the owner or occupier of such land or premises, and at`
  line `any other time, with the consent in writing of the owner of occupier of such land or premises, for the`
  line `purpose of the carrying out of such works or the making of such survey, examination or investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (38100)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 46
  title `Directors, Officers and other employees of a Corporation to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38100&sectionno=43&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `43. ^1[Directors],`
  line `^2[Officers and other employees] of a Corporation to be public servants.--All`
  line `^1[Directors] of a Corporation, and all ^2[officers and other employees] of a Corporation, whether appointed`
  line `by the State Government or the Corporation, shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in`
  line `pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act or of any other law, to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "members" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "officers and servants" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (38101)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38101&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the conditions and manner of appointment of Directors of a Corporation, the representation`
  line `in the Board of the Central and State Governments, and where shares are issued to other parties under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 23 of such shareholders and generally all matters relating to the constitution`
  line `of the Board;]`
  line
  line `^2[(b) remuneration, allowances or fees paid to the Directors of the Corporation or other persons`
  line `associated with the Board under section 10;]`
  line
  line `(c) the term of office of, the manner of filling casual vacancies among ^3[Directors] of the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(d) the number of ^3[Directors] necessary to constitute a quorum at a meeting of the ^4[Board];`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions of appointment and service and the scales of pay of the ^5[Managing Director,`
  line `the Chief Accounts Officer, the Financial Adviser or, as the case may be, the Chief Accounts`
  line `Officer-cum-Financial Adviser] of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(f) the number and term of office of, the allowances to be paid to, the procedure to be followed`
  line `by, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, members of an Advisory Council;`
  line
  line `^6[(ff) the procedure in accordance with which any stores may be declared obsolete under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 19;]`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which the shares of the Corporation shall be allotted, transferred or redeemed;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which the net profits of the Corporation shall be utilised;`
  line
  line `(i) the date by which, and the form in which, the budget shall be prepared and submitted in each`
  line `year under sub-section (1) of section 32;`
  line
  line `^7[(j) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be prepared;]`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which the returns, statistics or reports shall be submitted under section 35;`
  line
  line `(m) the procedure to be followed by an arbitral Tribunal under section 40;`
  line
  line `^9[(mm) the service of notices and orders under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "members" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "Chief Executive Officer or General Manager and the Chief Accounts Officer"`
  line `(w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 12, for clause (j) (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `8. Omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (38102)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38102&sectionno=45&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Corporation may with the previous sanction of ^1[the State`
  line `Government and by notification in the Official Gazette], make regulations, not inconsistent with this Act`
  line `and the rules made thereunder for the administration of the affairs of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which, and the purposes for which, persons may be associated with the ^2[Board]`
  line `^2[Board] under section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the time and place of meetings of a the ^2[Board] and the procedure to be followed in regard to`
  line `transaction of business at such meetings;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions of appointment and service and the scales of pay of officers and ^3[other`
  line `employees of the Corporation other than the Managing Director, the Chief Accounts Officer and the`
  line `Financial Adviser or, as the case may be, the Chief Accounts Officer-cum-Financial Adviser];`
  line
  line `^4[(d) the issue of passes to the employees of the Corporation and other persons under section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the grant of refund in respect of unused tickets and concessional passes under section 19.]`
  line
  line `^5[(f) the period after the expiration of which unclaimed articles or goods may be sold by public`
  line auction;
  line
  line `(g) the regulation of the carriage of passengers and goods in the road transport services of the`
  line Corporation.]
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the State Government" (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 63 of 1982, s. 16 and the Schedule, for "Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16 and the Schedule, ibid., for "servants of the Corporation, other than the Chief Executive Officer or General`
  line `General Manager and the Chief Accounts Officer" ( w.e.f. 13-11-1982).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 1959, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-9-1959).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_a:
  sectionId (38103)
  sectionNo 45A
  orderNo 49
  title `Every rule and regulation to be laid before State Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38103&sectionno=45A&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_45_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[45A. Every rule and regulation to be laid before State Legislature--Every rule and every`
  line `regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State`
  line Legislature.]
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (38104)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 50
  title `Penalty for breach of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38104&sectionno=46&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by rule, provide that the breach of`
  line `any rules made by it under section 44 ^1[or any regulations made by a Corporation under section 45] shall`
  line `be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and when the breach is a continuing`
  line `one, with a further fine not exceeding twenty rupees for every day after the date of the first conviction`
  line `during which the offender is proved to have persisted in the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (38105)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 51
  title `Special provisions relating to Bombay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38105&sectionno=47&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The body known as the Bombay State Road`
  line `Transport Corporation and the Board thereof, referred to in the notification of the Government of`
  line `Bombay, No. 1780/5, dated the 16th November, 1949 (hereinafter referred to as "the existing`
  line `corporation" and "Board" respectively) shall, notwithstanding any defect in, or invalidity of, the`
  line `enactment or order under which they were constituted, be deemed for all purposes to have been validly`
  line `constituted as if all the provisions of the said notification had been included and enacted in this section`
  line `and this section had been in force continuously on and from the said date, and accordingly--`
  line
  line `(a) all action by, and all transactions with, the existing Corporation or Board, including any`
  line `action or transaction by which any property, asset or right was acquired or any liability or obligation,`
  line `whether by contract or otherwise, was incurred, shall be deemed to have been validly and lawfully`
  line `taken or done; and`
  line
  line `(b) no suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government of Bombay or`
  line `any member of the Board or any officer or servant of the existing Corporation in respect of any action`
  line `taken by, or in relation to the setting up of, the existing Corporation or Board merely on the ground of`
  line `any defect in, or invalidity of, the enactment or order under which the existing Corporation or Board`
  line `was constituted.`
  line
  line `(2) On the establishment of a Corporation under section 3 in the State of Bombay (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as "the new Corporation"),--`
  line
  line `(a) the existing Corporation and Board shall be deemed to be dissolved and shall cease to`
  line function;
  line
  line `(b) all property and assets vesting in the existing Corporation shall vest in the new Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights, liabilities and obligations of the existing Corporation, whether arising out of any`
  line `contract or otherwise, shall be the rights, liabilities and obligations, respectively, of the new`
  line `Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(d) all licences and permits granted to, all contracts made with, and all instruments executed on`
  line `behalf of, the existing Corporation or Board shall be deemed to have been granted to, made with, or`
  line `executed on behalf, of, the new Corporation and shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47_a:
  sectionId (38106)
  sectionNo 47A
  orderNo 52
  title `Special provision for reconstitution or dissolution of certain Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38106&sectionno=47A&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_47_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[47A. Special provision for reconstitution or dissolution of certain Corporations.--(1) Where on`
  line `account of the reorganisation of States under the States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956),`
  line `^2[or any`
  line `other enactment relating to reorganisation of States, the whole or any part of a State in respect of which a`
  line `Corporation was, immediately before the day on which the reorganisation takes place,] functioning and`
  line `operating, is transferred on that day to another State and by reason of such transfer, it appears to the State`
  line `Government necessary or expedient that the Corporation should be reconstituted or re-organised in any`
  line `manner whatsoever or that it should be dissolved, the State Government may frame a scheme for the`
  line `reconstitution, reorganisation or dissolution of the Corporation including proposals regarding the formation of new Corporations the amalgamation of the Corporation with any other Corporation, body`
  line `corporate or a commercial undertaking of another State Government, the transfer of the assets, rights and`
  line `liabilities of the Corporation in whole or in part to any other Corporation, body corporate or a commercial`
  line `undertaking of another State Government, and the transfer or re-employment of any workmen of the`
  line `Corporation, and the State Government may forward the scheme to the Central Government for approval.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of framing any scheme under this sub-section, "State Government",--`
  line
  line `^3[(i) in relation to the Bombay State Road Transport Corporation, shall mean the`
  line `Government of the State of Maharashtra or of Gujarat as formed under the Bombay Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1960 (11 of 1960);`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to the PEPSU Road Transport Corporation, shall mean the Government of the State`
  line `of Punjab, as formed under the provisions of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956);]`
  line
  line `^4[(iii) in relation to the Assam State Road Transport Corporation, shall mean the Government of`
  line `the State of Assam or of Meghalaya as formed under the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) Act,`
  line `1971 (81 of 1971).]`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of any such scheme, the Central Government may, after consultation with the State`
  line `Governments concerned, approve the scheme with or without modifications and for the purpose of giving`
  line `effect to the approved scheme, the Central Government may, from time to time, make such order in`
  line `relation thereto as it thinks fit and every order so made shall have effect notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made under sub-section (2) may provide for all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the dissolution of the Corporation, notwithstanding anything contained in section 39;`
  line
  line `(b) the reconstitution or reorganisation, in any manner whatsoever, of the Corporation including`
  line `the establishment, where necessary, of more than one Corporation in any State;`
  line
  line `(c) the amalgamation of two or more Corporations, or of one Corporation with any other body`
  line `corporate or a commercial undertaking of any other State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the extension of the area for which the Corporation is established, or the exclusion of any area`
  line therefrom;
  line
  line `(e) the transfer, in whole or in part, of the assets, rights and liabilities of the Corporation`
  line `including the transfer of any licences or permits granted to the Corporation, to any other Corporation,`
  line `body corporate or a commercial undertaking of any other State Government, and the terms and`
  line `conditions of such transfer;`
  line
  line `(f) the transfer or re-employment of any workmen of the Corporation to, or by,`
  line `any such transferee, and, subject to the provisions of section 111 of the States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956 (37 of 1956),`
  line `^5[or any other enactment relating to reorganisation of States], the terms and`
  line `conditions of service applicable to such workmen after such transfer or re-employment;`
  line
  line `(g) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as may be necessary to give effect to`
  line `the approved scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an order is made under this section transferring the assets, rights and liabilities of any`
  line `Corporation, then, by virtue of that order, such assets, rights and liabilities of the Corporation shall vest`
  line `in, and be the assets, rights and liabilities of, the transferee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 87 of 1956, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-12-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 71, for "the whole or any part of a State in respect of which a Corporation was, immediately`
  line `before the 1st day of November, 1956," (w.e.f. 25-4-1960).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 25-4-1960).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 81 of 1971, s. 73 (w.e.f. 21-1-1972).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 71 (w.e.f. 25-4-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (38107)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 53
  title `Transitional provision relating to Bombay State Road Transport Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1960, s. 71 (w.e.f. 25-4-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38107&sectionno=48&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `^1[48. Transitional provision relating to Bombay State Road Transport Corporation.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 47A, it shall be lawful for the Government of the State of`
  line `Bombay to frame a scheme under sub-section (1) thereof and forward the same to the Central`
  line `Government before the 1st day of May, 1960, and in such a case, the power conferred on the Central`
  line `Government to make an order under sub-section (2) thereof may be exercised before that day but no order`
  line `so made shall take effect till that day.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (38108)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 54
  title `Prosecution and cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38108&sectionno=49&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[49. Prosecution and cognizance of offences.--(1) No court shall proceed to the trial of any offence`
  line `made punishable by or under this Act except on the complaint of, or on an information received from, the`
  line `General Manager of the new Corporation or a person authorised by him by general or special order in this`
  line `behalf in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) All offences against this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder, or any bye-law continued`
  line `thereunder, whether committed within or without the limits of the Union territory of Delhi, shall be`
  line `cognizable by a Magistrate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (38109)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 55
  title `Appointment of Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38109&sectionno=50&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `^1[50. Appointment of Magistrates.--(1) The State Government may appoint one or more magistrates`
  line `of the first or second class for the trial of offences against this Act or any rule or regulation made`
  line `thereunder or any bye-law continued thereunder and may prescribe the time and place at which such`
  line `magistrate or magistrates shall sit for the despatch of business.`
  line
  line `(2) Such magistrates and the members of their staff shall be paid such salary, pension, leave and other`
  line `allowances as may, from time to time, be fixed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The new Corporation shall out of its fund, pay to the State Government the amounts of the salary,`
  line `pension, leave and other allowances as fixed under sub-section (2) together with all other incidental`
  line `charges in connection with the establishments of the said magistrates.`
  line
  line `(4) Such Magistrates shall have jurisdiction over the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), all magistrates appointed`
  line `under this section shall be deemed to be magistrates appointed under section 12 of that Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (38110)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 56
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38110&sectionno=51&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Composition of offences.--(1) The General Manager of the new Corporation or any officer or`
  line `other employee specially empowered by him in this behalf in writing may, either before or after the`
  line `institution of the proceedings compound any offence made punishable by, or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded, the offender, if in custody, shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of the offence so compounded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (38111)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 57
  title `Limitation of time for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38111&sectionno=52&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Limitation of time for prosecution.--No person shall be liable to punishment for any offence`
  line `against this Act or any rule or regulation made thereunder or any bye-law continued thereunder, unless`
  line `complaint of such offence is made before a Magistrate within six months next after,--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the commission of such offence, or`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which the commission or existence of such offence was first brought to the notice`
  line `of the complainant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (38112)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of magistrate to hear cases in absence of accused when summoned to appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(a) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-9-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645&sectionId=38112&sectionno=53&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_30_42_00001_195064_1517807319645
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[53. Power of magistrate to hear cases in absence of accused when summoned to appear.--If any`
  line `person summoned to appear before a magistrate to answer a charge of an offence against this Act or any`
  line `rule or regulation made thereunder, or any bye-law continued thereunder, fails to appear at the time and`
  line `place mentioned in the summons, or on any date to which the hearing of the case is adjourned, the`
  line `magistrate may hear and determine the case in his absence, if--`
  line
  line `(a) service of the summons on such person is proved to his satisfaction, and`
  line
  line `(b) no sufficient cause is shown for the non-appearance of such person.]`
